# Multi-Site Deployment

This repository deploys **multiple sites** when synced to GitHub. A single codebase serves multiple companies; each deployment has its own Railway project, Supabase database, and environment variables.

## Current Sites

- **CAPCO Design Group** (RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN)
- **Rothco Built, LLC** (rothco-built.com or similar)

More sites will be added over time.

## Implications for Changes

1. **No site-specific hacks** – Code must work for all deployments. Use config, env vars, or feature flags instead of hardcoding for one company.
2. **Per-site config** – `SITE_CONFIG` env var, `SITE_CONFIG_JSON`, or `config-[company-slug].json` in `public/data/` or `dist/client/data/`.
3. **Post-deploy verification** – After sync, verify both CAPCO and Rothco (and any new sites) are working. See post-change-site-check.mdc and railway-env-config.mdc.

## Adding a New Site

1. Create a new Railway project (or branch).
2. Set env vars (Supabase, SITE_CONFIG, etc.).
3. Add `config-[company-slug].json` if not using SITE_CONFIG env.
4. Add to post-deploy check list.
